// Artifact Notification Parser
// Parses MCP tool response objects to extract structured artifact creation/update notifications.

FUNCTION parseArtifactNotification(mcpResponse) -> ArtifactNotification | null   EXPORT
  CALLS: extractArtifactType (parseArtifactNotification), extractNotificationType (parseArtifactNotification), extractArtifactName (parseArtifactNotification)
  Validate that mcpResponse is an object with success=true, a string id, a string previewUrl, and a string message.
  IF any required field is missing or invalid, return null.
  Determine the artifact type from the previewUrl (must contain 'diagram' or 'document').
  Determine the notification type from the message (must contain 'created' or 'updated').
  Extract the artifact name from the first quoted string in the message.
  IF any extraction fails or yields an empty name, return null.
  Return { type, artifactType, id, name }.

---

FUNCTION extractArtifactType(previewUrl) -> 'diagram' | 'document' | null
  Return 'diagram' if the URL contains 'diagram', 'document' if it contains 'document', else null.

---

FUNCTION extractNotificationType(message) -> 'created' | 'updated' | null
  Return 'created' if message contains 'created', 'updated' if it contains 'updated', else null.

---

FUNCTION extractArtifactName(message) -> string | null
  Extract and return the first double-quoted string from the message, or null if none found.
